{
  "background": "Refer to the study of retail prices of an automobile sold in the United States and Japan, Example 8.1. Another way to compare the mean retail prices for the two countries is to conduct a test of hypothesis. Use the information on the SPSS printout, Figure 8.1, to conduct the test. Use $\\alpha=.05$.",
